Do a global search for "h.t" in a string:

Copy
let str = "heat hit hot!";
let patt1 = /h.t/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The . metacharacter can find a single character, except newline or other line terminators.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
.	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("regexp.") or simply: /regexp./
Syntax with modifiers
Copy
new RegExp("regexp.", "g") or simply: /regexp./g
